<div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-337_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/flabbyarm--edited-1678068217613.jpg?v=1678068222" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/flabbyarm--edited-1678068217613.jpg?v=1678068222 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/flabbyarm--edited-1678068217613_1000x.jpg?v=1678068222 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/flabbyarm--edited-1678068217613_500x.jpg?v=1678068222 320w" width="1288" height="966" style="aspect-ratio:1288 / 966" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-338_"/><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-339_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-340_"></div></div></div><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-341_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-343_">Time may have passed, but we’re still obsessed with Michella Obama’s arms. That toned, strong look is impossible not to admire. Unfortunately, whether it’s because of age or hormones, excess tissue on the arms can get in the way of that, often also contributing to arm cellulite. If you’re hoping to tone up and get rid of cellulite on arms, this post is for you!<br><br>Whether you are looking for exercises, diet and nutrition tips, natural remedies, or over-the-counter treatments, this article has you covered.&nbsp;</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-344_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-346_">Table Of Contents</span></h2><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-347_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-348_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-iFMAIt bKYNsx pf-349_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-350_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-352_">1.&nbsp;<u>What Causes Cellulite On The Arms?  </u></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-353_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-355_">2. <u>How To Get Rid Of Arm Cellulite</u></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-593d" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-356_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-358_">3. <u>How To Prevent Arm Cellulite</u></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-28aa" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-359_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-361_">4. <u>Is It Arm Cellulite Or Skin?</u></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-28aa" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-iqVWFU eVpiLZ pf-362_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-364_">4. <u>Is It Arm Cellulite Or Skin?</u></span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-73dc" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-365_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-366_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-367_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-368_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-369_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-371_">What is Cellulite Subcision?&nbsp;</span></h2><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-372_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-373_"><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-374_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-376_">Subcision cellulite is basically a very minor surgical treatment. During the procedure, the doctor or surgeon slides a needle under the skin that’s fitted with a very small scalpel on its end. The scalpel cuts the fibrous bands that connect the skin to the underlying layer of fascia. Through this release, there is suddenly nothing for fat to bulge against, so the skin takes on a smoother appearance at the surface.&nbsp;<br><br>Subcision has a few main benefits that make it a popular procedure:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-377_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-378_">It is effective at reducing cellulite.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-380_">Unlike other surgical procedures, subcision has fairly minimal downtime.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-382_">The results are quite long-lasting.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-384_">FAQ for Subcision Cellulite Treatment</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5603" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-386_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-387_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-388_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-389_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-390_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-392_">Is Subcision for Cellulite Effective?&nbsp;</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-393_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">We already mentioned that subcision is effective at reducing cellulite, but let’s get a little more specific. Just how effective is it, and who will it work for?<br><br>Subcision is best for those who have cellulite that’s visible at all times, including at rest. If your cellulite is very mild and only visible when you’re moving or your body is angled in a specific way, subcision won’t help. It’s generally only performed on the buttocks or thighs. If you have arm cellulite or stomach cellulite, subcision is likely not an option.<br><br>The other thing about cellulite is that it’s multi-factorial. It’s not just caused by the connective bands that subcision tears apart. Its level of severity also depends on fat distribution and the quality of your skin. Sometimes, the skin looks dimpled because it’s lacking in collagen and elastin, in which case a treatment like subcision won’t make a big difference.<br><br>That’s why most doctors don’t perform subcision on its own. Instead, they combine it with other treatments like radiofrequency or dermal fillers. It’s important to keep this in mind because it’ll have an impact on the overall cost of your treatment, as well as whether you’ll need to come in for multiple appointments with your doctor.&nbsp;</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-395_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-397_">How is Subcision for Cellulite Performed?</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-398_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">So what is it like to get subcision for cellulite? It’s worth mentioning there are a few different types of subcision technologies with minor differences, but for the most part, this is the basic process:</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-400_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-401_">First, you’ll have a consultation with your doctor to discuss things like expectations and aftercare.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-403_">Your doctor will then mark the cellulite dimples while you’re standing, so they know exactly where they need to make cuts.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-405_">Anesthetic will then be injected into the target areas to prevent you from feeling any pain. <br> </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-407_">Your doctor will then carefully inserts the needle or subcision device under the skin where the cellulite dimple is located.<br> </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-409_">They will slide the needle side to side in a fan-like motion under the cellulite, in order to break up the connective bands. You can actually hear the bands snap as they’re cut! <br> </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-411_">Finally, your doctor will carefully remove the needle, put pressure on the cut to prevent bleeding, and then repeat the process over other areas of cellulite. <br> </li></ul><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-413_"></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-bebc" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-414_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-415_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-416_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-417_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-418_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-420_">Risks and Side Effects of Cellulite Subcision Treatment</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-421_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Bruising is basically guaranteed with subcision, and it’s not necessarily a bad thing. It can be a sign that your body is doing a better job reforming collagen. That said, there are also some potential side effects that are less pleasant.&nbsp;</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-423_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-424_">Pain immediately after the treatment may take a few days to fade.   </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-426_">Hematomas, which are very severe bruises that can take a lot longer to heal.   </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-428_">Scarring at the point where the needle pierced the skin.  <br> </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-430_">Infection is very uncommon but may occur if your aftercare is poor or if you don’t go to a reputable provider.   </li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-ebf6" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-432_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-433_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-434_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-435_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-436_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-438_">Evertone Cellulite Routine</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-439_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">If you ask us, subcision seems pretty extreme. As much as cellulite can be a pain in the butt, we’re not quite ready to have a surgeon cut under our skin to get rid of it… Especially when there are home treatments for cellulite that can also show results, and can work for everyone, including those with very mild cellulite.<br><br> Research shows that treatments like lymphatic massage and topical caffeine are actually very effective at reducing the appearance of cellulite, and the best part is that they don’t require going under the knife!<br><br>We’ve created an optimized body care routine that’s designed to visibly reduce cellulite within weeks. The combination of exfoliants, firming treatments, and a powerful Gua Sha massage come together to target your skin and its underlying layers, to fade the look of cellulite from top to bottom. No surgery needed! </p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-320b" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-441_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-442_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-443_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-444_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-445_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-447_">FAQ for Subcision Cellulite Treatment</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-448_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Is cellulite subcision safe?</p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-450_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Cellulite subcision, when performed correctly by an experienced doctor or surgeon, is considered quite safe. That said, as with any invasive procedure, it still has its side effects and risks, including bruising, scarring, and infection.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-452_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">How much does cellulite subcision cost?</p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-454_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">]Cellulite subcision usually costs between $2500 and $6000. The main price-deciding factor is how many cellulite dimples you’d like to treat - the more widespread the cellulite, the more you’ll need to pay.<br><br>As with any aesthetic treatments, costs can also vary pretty widely from location to location. It’s always better to pay a little more for a more experienced and reputable surgeon or doctor. <br> </p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-456_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">How long do the results of cellulite subcision last?</p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-458_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The results from subcision alone can last for at least a few years. Most research looks at results two years after treatment, but many doctors report that the skin can still appear smooth for three to five years after treatment. </p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-460_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Who is a good candidate for cellulite subcision treatment?</p><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-462_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The best candidate for subcision is someone with moderate to severe cellulite who is otherwise at a stable weight. There are actually grades that professionals use to analyze cellulite.<br><br>Subcision is best for those with grade two or grade three cellulite. That means that your dimples are visible no matter how your body is positioned, as opposed to those with grade one that might only have visible cellulite when sitting or pinching their skin.<br><br>As for contraindications, subcision is not recommended for pregnant women, anyone who’s very prone to scarring, those suffering from bleeding disorders or who are taking medications that prevent blood clotting, and more. Your surgeon should consult a thorough consultation with you to make sure that you’re a good candidate. </p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-2814" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-464_ pf-lg-hide pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-465_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-466_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-467_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-468_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-470_">FAQ for Belly Cellulite</span></h2><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-471_">Are there any exercises that can help reduce cellulite on the stomach?&nbsp;</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-473_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Probably not. There’s a myth that core exercises will help reduce cellulite and stomach fat, but in reality, it’s <a href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/targeted-weight-loss" target="_self"><u>impossible to spot-reduce fat</u></a>.<br><br>Strength training in general is excellent for toning your body as a whole, while cardio can help you lose fat and improve your body’s overall circulation. Overtime, and as long as weight loss is gradual, this may help improve the look of cellulite on your stomach.&nbsp;</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-475_">Can diet and nutrition play a role in reducing cellulite on the stomach?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-477_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Yes, diet and nutrition can play a role in reducing cellulite on the stomach. A diet high in processed foods, sugar, and unhealthy fats can increase your risk of developing cellulite. That said, losing weight through dieting does not guarantee cellulite reduction.&nbsp;</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-479_">Is cellulite on the stomach more common in women or men?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-481_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Cellulite is much more common in women than in men, and that also applies to cellulite on the belly. It’s estimated that around 90% of women have cellulite, but only around 10% of men. The theory is that women’s hormones impact how the connective tissue under our skin is structured, which is what leads to cellulite in women.&nbsp;</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-483_">Are there any over-the-counter creams or gels that can help with cellulite on the stomach?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-485_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Yes, some over-the-counter creams and gels can help reduce the appearance of cellulite on the stomach. Look for products that contain ingredients like retinol and caffeine, which can help improve the look of skin elasticity and diminish the appearance of cellulite with regular use.</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-487_">How does age affect cellulite on the belly?</h3><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-489_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As we age, our skin loses elasticity and becomes less firm, which can make cellulite more noticeable. Additionally, hormonal changes, reduced circulation, and changes in body fat distribution can all contribute to cellulite formation as we age.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-dfdc" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-491_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-492_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-493_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-494_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-495_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:3"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-496_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/avatar1146e09cf01a5205043db6a6499887c1-1677185916858.jpg?v=1677185919" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0621/2272/1446/t/26/assets/avatar1146e09cf01a5205043db6a6499887c1-1677185916858.jpg?v=1677185919 1536w" width="1024" height="1024" style="aspect-ratio:1024 / 1024" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-497_"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:9"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-498_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-499_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-501_">Adriana Bailey</span></h3><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-502_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-504_">Meet our talented content writer Adriana Bailey. She has dedicated her career to creating informative, engaging, and relevant content for readers who want to learn more about the latest beauty products and techniques.In her free time, Adriana enjoys experimenting with new makeup styles or researching inspiration in the latest beauty trends.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-dd2f" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-505_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-506_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-507_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-508_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-509_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-510_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-511_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"></div><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-512_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-513_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-514_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-516_">Is Subcision for Cellulite Effective?&nbsp;</span></h2><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-517_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-519_">We already mentioned that subcision is effective at reducing cellulite, but let’s get a little more specific. Just how effective is it, and who will it work for?<br><br>Subcision is best for those who have cellulite that’s visible at all times, including at rest. If your cellulite is very mild and only visible when you’re moving or your body is angled in a specific way, subcision won’t help. It’s generally only performed on the buttocks or thighs. If you have arm cellulite or stomach cellulite, subcision is likely not an option.&nbsp;<br><br>The other thing about cellulite is that it’s multi-factorial. It’s not just caused by the connective bands that subcision tears apart. Its level of severity also depends on fat distribution and the quality of your skin. Sometimes, the skin looks dimpled because it’s lacking in collagen and elastin, in which case a treatment like subcision won’t make a big difference.<br><br>That’s why most doctors don’t perform subcision on its own. Instead, they combine it with other treatments like radiofrequency or dermal fillers. It’s important to keep this in mind because it’ll have an impact on the overall cost of your treatment, as well as whether you’ll need to come in for multiple appointments with your doctor.&nbsp;</span></p></div></div></div></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-78dd" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-520_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-521_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-522_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-523_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-524_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-525_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-526_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"></div><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-527_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-528_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-529_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-531_">How is Subcision for Cellulite Performed?</span></h2><p class="sc-bBHHxi fhourC pf-532_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">So what is it like to get subcision for cellulite? It’s worth mentioning there are a few different types of subcision technologies with minor differences, but for the most part, this is the basic process: </p></div></div></div><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-534_">First, you’ll have a consultation with your doctor to discuss things like expectations and aftercare. <span style="font-weight: 700;"></span></li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-536_">Your doctor will then mark the cellulite dimples while you’re standing, so they know exactly where they need to make cuts.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-538_">Anesthetic will then be injected into the target areas to prevent you from feeling any pain.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-540_">Your doctor will then carefully inserts the needle or subcision device under the skin where the cellulite dimple is located.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-542_">They will slide the needle side to side in a fan-like motion under the cellulite, in order to break up the connective bands. You can actually hear the bands snap as they’re cut!   </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-544_">Finally, your doctor will carefully remove the needle, put pressure on the cut to prevent bleeding, and then repeat the process over other areas of cellulite.   </li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-fde5" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-546_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gjNHFA gwWIgj"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-547_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-548_"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-549_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-550_"><h2 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dPiLbb JgHoc pf-551_">Risks and Side Effects of Cellulite Subcision Treatment</h2><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-553_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-555_">Bruising is basically guaranteed with subcision, and it’s not necessarily a bad thing. It can be a sign that your body is doing a better job reforming collagen. That said, there are also some potential side effects that are less pleasant.&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 700;"></span></span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-556_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-557_">Pain immediately after the treatment may take a few days to fade. <span style="font-weight: 700;"></span></li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-559_">Hematomas, which are very severe bruises that can take a lot longer to heal.  </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-561_">Scarring at the point where the needle pierced the skin.   </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-563_">Infection is very uncommon but may occur if your aftercare is poor or if you don’t go to a reputable provider.    </li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gUQvok iVVDxu pf-565_"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-b035" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fmciRz bheIgq pf-566_ 